HEADWORD: Elfish
<hw>Elf"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or relating to the elves;
elflike; implike; weird; scarcely human; mischievous, as though caused
by elves.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Elfish</xex> light.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>elfish</qex> intelligence that was so familiar an
expression on her small physiognomy.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elfishly</ent>⟦br⟧
